.TH MFUTIL-ART 1 2025-01-01 "mfutil 0.1.1"
.SH NAME
mfutil-art \- Extract and manage album art for your music library
.SH SYNOPSIS
.B mfutil art
.RI [ OPTIONS ]
.SH DESCRIPTION
The
.B art
subcommand extracts embedded album artwork from music files and downloads
missing cover art from online sources like MusicBrainz and AudioDB. It also
creates folder icons for easy visual identification of albums in file managers.
.SH OPTIONS
.TP
.BR \-m ", " \-\-music-dir " " \fIPATH\fR
Specify the music directory path (default: ~/Music)
.TP
.B \-h, \-\-help
Print help information
.SH FEATURES
.TP
Extract embedded artwork from audio files (FLAC, MP3, etc.)
.TP
Download missing cover art from MusicBrainz
.TP
Fallback to AudioDB for additional cover sources
.TP
Set folder icons for visual album identification
.TP
Create artist image placeholders when art is unavailable
.SH ENVIRONMENT
.TP
.B AUDIODB_API_KEY
API key for AudioDB cover art service
.TP
.B PEXELS_API_KEY
API key for Pexels image service (for placeholders)
.SH FILES
Extracted artwork is saved as cover.jpg in album directories
.SH EXAMPLES
.TP
Process album art for default music directory:
.B mfutil art
.TP
Process album art for custom directory:
.B mfutil art --music-dir /path/to/music
.SH SEE ALSO
.BR mfutil (1),
.BR mfutil-sync (1),
.BR mfutil-all (1)
.SH NOTES
This command requires internet access to download cover art from online services.